  "text": "Research shows that the best, unconfounded indicator of tie-strength is subjective: a feeling of intimacy and closeness [CITATION_1] . And that variable cannot be inferred merely from network structure or frequency of interaction; rather, uncovering it requires other methods such as more extensive content analysis of the communication between the alters or interpersonal research techniques such as surveys or interviews.",
